<pageBreakToken id="087201595649DC9C3D1315CDF786B89F" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" start="start">Astelia</pageBreakToken>
Banks &amp; Sol. ex R.Br. subg. Astelia
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C05B4ED3E34FB8D1C71C73AE33CC2031" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="note">
<paragraph id="E3289E216094CA745DE8718C4CF9D48F" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F5B061366BC38B9ED4FF3ACD45EBFA9" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Flowers with a very short perianth tube (0.1-0.8 mm); anthers dorsifixed, versatile; ovary unilocular; seeds ovoid; funicle long, curved, with mucilaginous funicular hairs poorly developed that surround but do not adhere to the seed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F658FD7BAC3BEE1B107CBC3691D07410" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D4A8C6BE0BCFFC3E44ED6607486D99E8" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0E684778C489353116E1BE80CFC543D" pageId="4" pageNumber="109">
Molecular (
<bibRefCitation id="CF643854B9F8EF9C40D3BA3B55F29775" author="Birch, JL" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="102 - 115" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" refId="B2" refString="Birch, JL, Keeley, SC, Morden, CW, 2012. Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s.l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 102 - 115, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" title="Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s. l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" volume="65" year="2012">Birch et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and morphology-based phylogenetic analyses (Birch unpublished PhD thesis 2011) indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="B8B0536A084DBE751FC5ECF921AD6DEB" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Astelia) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="veratroides" subGenus="Astelia" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Astelia</taxonomicName>
, as circumscribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="D6638DD7A12B5C7744C1983115D82DA3" author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, is polyphyletic. 
<taxonomicName id="E702E4816114577B36B7D833440E8A8A" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Astelia) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="veratroides" subGenus="Astelia" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Astelia</taxonomicName>
is revised to include 
<taxonomicName id="3D82F695CDEB66DE0CD80A05D8151E9F" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Palaeastelia" species="veratroides" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Palaeastelia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="19B226259F647B52B5B6E422F3C56523" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Astelia" species="veratroides" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Astelia</taxonomicName>
, which form a clade. 
<taxonomicName id="3699C8CCC8B98EA920D68FDFB999649A" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Desmoneuron" species="veratroides" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Desmoneuron</taxonomicName>
is placed in a different clade and it is excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="1837F625E2D3D0A8970050D5F1DA2D8E" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Astelia) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="veratroides" subGenus="Astelia" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Astelia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
